The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Saturday, June 04, 2005 

 Madrid: Dutch international striker Patrick Kluivert has agreed to sign a three-year contract with Valencia, the Primera Liga side said on Friday. The 28-year-old, who will arrive on a free transfer from English club Newcastle United, is due to undergo a medical at Valencia on Thursday.

 Kluivert joined Newcastle on a three-year deal after being released by Barcelona at the end of the 2003-04 season. He failed to live up to expectations, starting 25 games in all competitions and scoring 13 goals. 

 Kozhikode: Former sprint queen P.T. Usha?s project, Usha School of Athletics and Kerala-based Regional Agro Industrial Development Corporation (Raidco) on Friday signed am MoU that will ensure regular financial support to the school to sustain its activities. The school, expected to be ready by the year-end, would receive consumables from Raidco to the tune of Rs 2,500 every month. 

 Madrid: Atletico Madrid defender Sergi announced his retirement on Friday after 12 years as a professional in the Spanish top flight.

 ?I think it?s the right time to put football to one side,? the 33-year-old left back said in Madrid. ?You have to know when to stop and I think now that time has come. I want to thank everyone who has helped me play football at the two clubs I have played at during my career. 

 ?I don?t know what I will be doing in the future, but I am now trying to get my qualifications as a football coach.?

